This objection may be solved either nega· tively or in the affirmative. Man is that which is white and that which is black3 but Man is not white and black. For, as a universal, this term can receive no predicates but such as are essential to human nature: and it is evident that neither whiteness nor blackness are thus essential (p. 4ο, l. 15 to p. 42, l. ὁ).
